etti), Op. 68", "w": "10230"}, {"t": "Souvenir de la Havane, Op. 39", "w": "12598"}, {"t": "Symphony No. 2, \"Á Montevideo\"", "w": "49669"}, {"t": "A Continuous Performance", "w": "97179"}, {"t": "Tremolo, Op. 58", "w": "17626"}, {"t": "L’étincelle, Op. 21", "w": "70938"}, {"t": "Pasquinade, Op. 59", "w": "51690"}, {"t": "Suis-moi!, Op. 45", "w": "123010"}, {"t": "Le banjo, Op. 15", "w": "10753"}, {"t": "The Last Hope, Op. 16", "w": "53867"}, {"t": "Grande tarantelle for Piano 4-Hands, Op. 67", "w": "122803"}, {"t": "The Banjo, Op. 15", "w": "14984"}, {"t": "Overture de Guillaume Tell (after Rossini)", "w": "14983"}, {"t": "Manchega, Op. 38", "w": "27750"}], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Loren Schoenberg", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "about the great lives of the nineteenth century and about Gottschalk, Louis Moreau Gottschalk", "doc_title": "Loren Schoenberg interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 14, 2019", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/loren-schoenberg-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-14-2019"}, {"speaker": "Victor Rendon", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "There was a guy named Gottschalk. ... And he was influenced by that, or he actually went to South America and died or something, if I’m correct. ... That’s my opinion from what I’ve read and listened to over the years.", "doc_title": "Victor Rendon interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clinton, New York, November 15, 2019 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/victor-rendon-interviewed-monk-rowe-clinton-new-york-november-15-2019-interview"}]}